 Reference Types :- 
 -------------------------

 1 %TYPE 
 2 %ROWTYPE

 %TYPE :- 
 ------------

  => %type is used to refer column datatype and size
  => used to match variable datatype & size with column datatype and size

 ex :-     vempno        emp.empno%TYPE;
             vename        emp.ename%TYPE;
             vsal               emp.sal%TYPE;

 =>  in the above example whatever datatype and size declared for sal column in emp table
       the same type and size assigned to variable vsal.

  %ROWTYPE :- 
   -------------------

   => used to refer record type 
   => %rowtype reduces no of variables required in the program and reduces complexity
   => a record from table can be assigned to rowtype variable
 
           ex :-    e        emp%ROWYPE; 

  => a row from emp table can be assigned to variable "e" 

      SELECT *  INTO e 
      FROM emp 
      WHERE empno = 7369 ; 

       e
       empno  ename   job    	mgr   hiredate  sal   comm   deptno
       7369     turner    sales	                       800   null	20

   => from "e" individual field values are accessed by using   rowtypevar.fieldname

              e.sal   =>  800
              e.ename => turner

